Quattro Formaggi Pizza:

Pizza dough
Tomato sauce
Mozzarella cheese
Gorgonzola cheese
Fontina cheese
Parmesan cheese

Preparation:

Roll out the pizza dough into your desired shape.
Spread a thin layer of tomato sauce evenly on the dough.
Sprinkle shredded mozzarella cheese over the sauce.
Crumble gorgonzola cheese and distribute it over the pizza.
Place slices of fontina cheese on top of the other cheeses.
Sprinkle grated parmesan cheese over the pizza.
Preheat your oven to 450°F (230°C) and bake the pizza for around 12-15 minutes until the cheese is melted and bubbly, and the crust is golden.
Remove from the oven, let it cool for a moment, slice, and enjoy the delicious Quattro Formaggi pizza!
